    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-21T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="573"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/8–1744:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-21T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1669. Department and FEA have given careful consideration to Legation’s 3147,
                    August 17, midnight, repeated to London as 908. They appreciate your efforts to
                    obtain piston ring embargo.</p>
                <p>In view of present situation, we desire that you abstain from initiating further
                    discussions on this point. Should Davy Robertson press for a decision, you are
                    instructed to withdraw request for embargo originally made last March,
                    explaining at your discretion that we are unable to make available at this time
                    the electric furnace, Wasp piston rings, nor additional funds.</p>
                <p>It may be pointed out that the Swedes have failed since mid-April to accept our
                    offer of $75,000.00 in return for a total embargo.</p>
                <p>Sent to Stockholm, repeated to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
